<br>
Ok... you have to put a few things they have said together to understand where we are going.  Today's patch finally made it all clear.<br>
<br>
1) They have been saying that they want to return to the Kunark style of game play where the battles are short and your skills and tactics within the first minute will determine if you succeed or not.  The battles will not last long periods of time like in Luclin encounters.<br>
<br>
2) They nerfed the monks ability to tank by lowering their defensive abilities.  This makes it so that a monk does not want to out agro a warrior.<br>
<br>
3) They nerfed the wizards manaburn.  This makes it so that you can't win a short Kunark style battle with a group of wizards just manaburning.<br>
<br>
4) They increased the warriors ability to agro by upgrading their taunt.<br>
<br>
5) They increased the warriors ability to NOT get hit by increasing their dodge.<br>
<br>
6) They increased the warriors ability to agro by upgrading their damage mitigation.<br>
<br>
7) They increased the overall maximum hit points that a warrior can have (post Planes of Power release).<br>
<br>
Add it all up, and the picture is clear.  They have increased the abilities of the warrior to tank because the Planes of Power encounters are DESIGNED around a warrior tanking the mob!<br>
<br>
As I said before... WE ARE BACK!  YES!!!!  Long Live The Tank!<br>
